impl<T> Drop for SafeArray<T> { /// Ensures proper cleanup of all resources /// /// This is safe because it: /// - Only drops initialized elements (0..len) /// - Deallocates with the same parameters used for allocation /// - Handles the zero-capacity case correctly fn drop(&mut self) { // Drop all initialized elements for i in 0..self.len { unsafe { // SAFETY: i < len, so element is initialized ptr::drop_in_place(self.ptr.add(i)); } } // Deallocate memory if self.capacity > 0 { unsafe { // SAFETY: // - ptr was allocated with allocate_array(capacity) // - All elements have been dropped above // - We're calling this exactly once deallocate_array(self.ptr, self.capacity); } } }
}
